()SailPoint IdentityIQ me AuditEvent ek object hota hai jo system me hone wale actions ko log (audit)
karne ke liye use hota hai.
Jaise:-
login
access change
role assign
provisioning
sab events audit log me store hote hain.
AuditEvent system me hone wale events ko record karta hai.

2️⃣ Important Methods of AuditEvent:-

3️⃣ setSource():-
Event kaha se generate hua.
event.setSource("WebUI");
Example sources:-
WebUI
Workflow
Provisioning
API

4️⃣ getSource():-
Source return karta hai.
String src = event.getSource();

5️⃣ setTarget():-
Kis identity ya object pe action hua.
event.setTarget("Rahul");

6️⃣ getTarget():-
Target return karta hai.
String target = event.getTarget();

7️⃣ setString1():-
Custom data store karne ke liye.
event.setString1("FinanceRole");

8️⃣ getString1():-
Custom value return karta hai.
String value = event.getString1();

9️⃣ setString2():-
Second custom field.
event.setString2("Access Granted");

🔟 getString2():-
String value = event.getString2();

1️⃣1️⃣ setAttribute():-
Extra attributes set karta hai.
event.setAttribute("Application", "SAP");

1️⃣2️⃣ getAttribute():-
Attribute value return karta hai.
String app = event.getAttribute("Application");

4️⃣ getSource():-
Ye method event ka source return karta hai.
Matlab event kaha se generate hua.
Example sources ho sakte hain:-
WebUI
Workflow
Provisioning
API

6️⃣ getTarget():-
Ye method target object ya identity return karta hai.
Matlab kis user ya object pe action hua.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
📌 AuditEvent ka matlab kya hai?
AuditEvent ek audit logging class hai
Ye system me hone wale important actions/events ko record (log) karta hai.

🔥 Simple samajh:-
👉 Jab bhi system me kuch important hota hai:-
Request create hua
Approval hua
Access grant/revoke hua
Login/logout hua
➡️ Ye sab events AuditEvent me store hote hain.

⚙️ Ye kya track karta hai?
AuditEvent ke through system ye sab track karta hai:
Kisne action kiya (user)
Kya action hua
Kab hua (timestamp)
Kis object par hua (request / identity / role)
Result kya tha (success / failure)

()AuditEvent Methods List
getId()
setId(String id)
getAction()
setAction(String action)
getString3()
setString3(String value)
getString4()
setString4(String value)
getAttributeName()
setAttributeName(String name)
getAttributeValue()
setAttributeValue(String value)
getAttributes()
setAttributes(Attributes attributes)
getCreated()
setCreated(Date date)
getModified()
setModified(Date date)

getOwner()
setOwner(Identity owner)

getApplication()
setApplication(Application app)
getAccountName()
setAccountName(String name)

getInstance()
setInstance(String instance)

getTrackingId()
setTrackingId(String trackingId)

getInterface()
setInterface(String iface)

toMap()
fromMap(Map map)
toXml()
fromXml(String xml)
clone()
equals(Object obj)
hashCode()
toString()
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()getId() / setId(String id):-
Har audit event ka unique ID hota hai.
Isse event ko identify karte hain DB ya logs me.
-------------------------------------------------------
🔹 Action:-
getAction() / setAction(String action):-
Ye batata hai kya action hua hai.
Example:
"Create"
"Update"
"Delete"
"Login"
-----------------------------------------------
🔹 Extra String Fields (Custom Use):-
getString3() / setString3(String value)
getString4() / setString4(String value)
Ye custom fields hote hain.
Developer apne hisaab se data store kar sakta hai.
Example:-
auditEvent.setString3("ManagerApproval");
auditEvent.setString4("HighPriority");
------------------------------------------------
()getAttributeName() / setAttributeName(String name):-
Kaunsa attribute change hua (field name).
Example: "email", "role", "department"

()getAttributeValue() / setAttributeValue(String value):-
Us attribute ka naya value kya hai,jo change hua.
Example:-
setAttributeName("email");
setAttributeValue("user@gmail.com");
----------------------------------------------------------
🔹 Time Tracking:-
getCreated() / setCreated(Date date):-
Event kab create hua.
getModified() / setModified(Date date):-
Event kab last update hua.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 Attributes Map kyu store karta hai?
Simple line me:-
👉 Ek hi audit event me multiple data flexible way me store karne ke liye.

🔹 Problem kya hoti agar Attributes na ho?
Soch:-
Agar sirf ye fields hoti:-
attributeName
attributeValue
👉 Tab tu sirf ek hi field ka change store kar pata
Example:-
email → user@gmail.com

❌ Problem:-
Agar ek hi request me multiple changes hue:-
role → Admin
status → Active
department → IT
Toh 3 alag audit events banana padta ❌ (inefficient)

🔹 Attributes Map (Advanced):-
getAttributes() / setAttributes(Attributes attributes)
Multiple attributes ko ek saath key-value pair me store karta hai.

Example:-
✔️ Multiple data ek hi event me:-
Attributes attrs = new Attributes();
attrs.put("role", "Admin");
attrs.put("status", "Active");
attrs.put("department", "IT");
auditEvent.setAttributes(attrs);
👉 Ek hi audit event me sab changes store ho gaye
--------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 Real-world samajh:-
Scenario:-
User Rahul ne apna password change kiya

👉 AuditEvent me:-
Action → Password Change
Owner → Rahul
-----------------------------------
🔹 Methods ka meaning:-

()setOwner(Identity owner)
Audit event ka owner set karta hai
Matlab: “ye event kis user ke naam pe log ho raha hai”
getOwner()
Audit event ka owner return karta hai
Matlab: “ye event kis user ka hai”
🔹 Example (simple)
Identity user = context.getObjectByName(Identity.class, "rahul");

AuditEvent event = new AuditEvent();
event.setAction("Update Account");
event.setOwner(user);

👉 Yaha:-
Action = Update Account
Owner = Rahul
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 getApplication() / setApplication(Application app):-
👉 Matlab:-
Ye batata hai kaunsa application (target system) involved hai.
Example: AD, SAP, Salesforce, etc.

()setApplication(Application app):-
AuditEvent me application set karta hai
Matlab: “ye event kis system me hua”

()getApplication():-
Kaunsa application involved tha → return karta hai
✅ Example:
Application app = context.getObjectByName(Application.class, "Active Directory");
auditEvent.setApplication(app);
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 getAccountName() / setAccountName(String name):-
👉 Matlab:-
Ye batata hai kaunsa account (username) affected hai us application me

()setAccountName(String name):-
Account ka naam set karta hai
Matlab: “kis account pe action hua”

()getAccountName():-
Account name return karta hai
----------------------------------------------
🔹 getInstance() / setInstance(String instance) matlab:-
👉 Instance = specific environment / system instance / server context
Ye batata hai ki ye audit event kis instance me hua
Matlab ek hi application ke multiple environments ho sakte hain:
Dev
Test
Prod
Ya different servers

🔹 Methods ka meaning:-
setInstance(String instance)
AuditEvent me instance ka naam set karta hai
Matlab: “ye event kis environment/system instance me hua”
getInstance():-
Wo instance return karta hai jaha event hua
--------------------------------------------------------------
🔹 getTrackingId() / setTrackingId() matlab:-
👉 TrackingId = ek unique identifier jo ek request/flow ko track karta hai
Ye use hota hai poore flow ko link karne ke liye
Matlab: ek hi request ke multiple events ho sakte hain → un sabko ek ID se connect kar dete hain
🔹 Methods ka meaning:-
()setTrackingId(String trackingId):-
AuditEvent me tracking ID set karta hai
Matlab: “ye event kis request/flow ka part hai”

()getTrackingId():-
Wo tracking ID return karta hai
Matlab: “ye event kis flow se related hai”
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
interface:-ye batata hai action kis interface (entry point) se aaya hai. 😎

🔹 getInterface() / setInterface() matlab:-
👉 Interface = kis medium se action perform hua
Matlab: user ne kaam kahan se kiya
Ye identify karta hai entry source

🔹 Methods ka meaning:-

()setInterface(String iface):-
AuditEvent me interface set karta hai
Matlab: “ye action kis interface se trigger hua”

()getInterface():-
Wo interface return karta hai

🔹 Common Interface Values:-
"UI" → User ne portal (web UI) se action kiya
"API" → REST API se request aayi
"Workflow" → Workflow engine ne action trigger kiya
"Task" → Scheduled task/job se action hua
"LCM" → Lifecycle Manager se aaya
🔹 Example:-
auditEvent.setInterface("UI");
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
()toMap():-
Object ko Map (key-value pairs) me convert karta hai
Easy hota hai data ko process ya log karna
Map map = auditEvent.toMap();

()fromMap(Map map):-
Map se wapas object create karta hai
auditEvent.fromMap(map);

()toXml():-
Object ko XML format me convert karta hai
Mostly export, logging ya integration ke liye
String xml = auditEvent.toXml();

()fromXml(String xml):-
XML se wapas object create karta hai
auditEvent.fromXml(xml);

()clone():-
Object ka exact copy (duplicate) banata hai
AuditEvent copy = (AuditEvent) auditEvent.clone();

()equals(Object obj):-
Check karta hai 2 objects same hain ya nahi
auditEvent.equals(otherEvent);

()hashCode():-
Object ka unique hash value generate karta hai
Mostly use hota hai HashMap, HashSet me

()toString():-
Object ko readable string format me convert karta hai
Debugging me useful
System.out.println(auditEvent.toString());

import sailpoint.object.AuditEvent;
import sailpoint.object.Attributes;
import java.util.Map;
import java.util.Date;

public class TestAudit {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        // Create AuditEvent
        AuditEvent event = new AuditEvent();
        event.setId("1");
        event.setAction("Create Account");
        event.setAttributeName("role");
        event.setAttributeValue("Admin");
        event.setCreated(new Date());

        Attributes attrs = new Attributes();
        attrs.put("status", "Active");
        attrs.put("location", "India");
        event.setAttributes(attrs);

        // 🔹 toMap()
        Map map = event.toMap();
        System.out.println("Map Output: " + map);

        // 🔹 fromMap()
        AuditEvent newEvent = new AuditEvent();
        newEvent.fromMap(map);
        System.out.println("FromMap Output: " + newEvent.toString());

        // 🔹 toXml()
        String xml = event.toXml();
        System.out.println("XML Output:\n" + xml);

        // 🔹 clone()
        AuditEvent cloned = (AuditEvent) event.clone();
        System.out.println("Cloned Output: " + cloned.toString());

        // 🔹 equals()
        System.out.println("Equals Check: " + event.equals(cloned));

        // 🔹 hashCode()
        System.out.println("HashCode: " + event.hashCode());

        // 🔹 toString()
        System.out.println("ToString Output: " + event.toString());
    }
}
🔹 Expected Output (Simplified):-
✅ toMap() Output:-
Map Output: {
  id=1,
  action=Create Account,
  attributeName=role,
  attributeValue=Admin,
  attributes={status=Active, location=India},
  created=Mon Mar 23 12:00:00 IST 2026
}
✅ fromMap() Output:-
FromMap Output: AuditEvent[id=1, action=Create Account, attributeName=role, attributeValue=Admin]

✅ toXml() Output:-
<AuditEvent>
  <id>1</id>
  <action>Create Account</action>
  <attributeName>role</attributeName>
  <attributeValue>Admin</attributeValue>
  <attributes>
    <entry key="status" value="Active"/>
    <entry key="location" value="India"/>
  </attributes>
</AuditEvent>
✅ clone() Output:-
Cloned Output: AuditEvent[id=1, action=Create Account, attributeName=role]

✅ equals() Output:-
Equals Check: true

✅ hashCode() Output:-
HashCode: 12345678

✅ toString() Output:-
ToString Output: AuditEvent[id=1, action=Create Account, attributeName=role, attributeValue=Admin]